PART B: NORMALIZATION (10 Marks)

Overview:
The SHOP_DATA relation is decomposed from an unnormalized flat structure — containing 26 mixed attributes across suppliers, watches, orders, clients, employees, warranties, and payments — into 7 distinct third normal form (3NF) tables.
This process eliminates repeating groups and redundant data (1NF), removes partial dependencies where single-key relations already satisfied 2NF, and resolves transitive dependencies to ensure all non-key attributes depend solely on their respective primary keys (3NF).

Initial Unnormalized Relation (UNF)

SHOP_DATA
(SupplierID, SupplierName, ContactAddress, PhoneNo, WatchID, WatchName, Price, Material, OrderID, Status, Pending, TotalPrice, ClientID, ClientName, Email, PhoneNumber, EmployeeID, EmployeeName, Position, WarrantyNo, WarrantyExpireDate, IssueDate, PaymentID, PaymentDate, PaymentAmount, PaymentMethod)

This structure contains redundant and dependent attributes.

Functional Dependencies

SupplierID → SupplierName, ContactAddress, PhoneNo

WatchID → Name, Price, Material, SupplierID

OrderID → Status, Pending, TotalPrice, ClientID, EmployeeID

ClientID → Name, Email, PhoneNumber

EmployeeID → EmployeeName, Position, PhoneNumber

WarrantyNo → WarrantyExpireDate, IssueDate

PaymentID → PaymentDate, PaymentAmount, PaymentMethod

FIRST NORMAL FORM (1NF)

Tables:

Supplier(SupplierID, SupplierName, ContactAddress, PhoneNo)

Watch(WatchID, Name, Price, Material, SupplierID)

Order(OrderID, Status, Pending, TotalPrice, ClientID, EmployeeID)

Client(ClientID, Name, Email, PhoneNumber)

Employee(EmployeeID, EmployeeName, Position, PhoneNumber)

Warranty(WarrantyNo, WarrantyExpireDate, IssueDate)

Payment(PaymentID, PaymentDate, PaymentAmount, PaymentMethod)

Second Normal Form (2NF)

Remove partial dependencies by ensuring all non-key attributes depend on the entire primary key.

All relations now have single primary keys.

Third Normal Form (3NF)

Remove transitive dependencies.

Final tables remain independent with attributes depending only on their primary key.

Final Relations in 3NF

Supplier
(PK SupplierID, SupplierName, ContactAddress, PhoneNo)

Watch
(PK WatchID, Name, Price, Material, FK SupplierID)

Client
(PK ClientID, Name, Email, PhoneNumber)

Employee
(PK EmployeeID, EmployeeName, Position, PhoneNumber)

Order
(PK OrderID, Status, Pending, TotalPrice, FK ClientID, FK EmployeeID)

Warranty
(PK WarrantyNo, WarrantyExpireDate, IssueDate)

Payment
(PK PaymentID, PaymentDate, PaymentAmount, PaymentMethod)

